# But tomorrow there'll be hell to pay

47:50.578 --> 47:52.286
# People listen attentively

47:52.414 --> 47:54.371
# I mean about future calamity

47:54.499 --> 47:57.120
# I used to think the idea was obsolete

47:57.252 --> 48:00.253
# Until I heard the old man stamping his feet #

48:19.566 --> 48:23.943
Nobody died.
Is that, like, kosher?

48:24.070 --> 48:26.146
It's not 2.36 yet.

48:37.167 --> 48:40.002
- Bank's closed.
- ATM's busted. I gotta cash my cheque.

48:40.128 --> 48:42.037
Sorry, bank's closed.

48:44.382 --> 48:46.956
Come on, man.

49:07.947 --> 49:11.032
You were right, it was the banana peel.

49:14.662 --> 49:16.951
Dude, that is fucked up!

49:19.668 --> 49:21.577
Wait a sec.

49:21.711 --> 49:23.870
- Is that me?
- Yeah.

49:24.005 --> 49:26.675
Sorry, man, you're dead.

49:29.928 --> 49:31.837
No way.

49:34.015 --> 49:36.304
Oh, I just got paid.

49:37.018 --> 49:39.141
Oh, man, this sucks!

49:40.522 --> 49:42.349
Do you live alone?

49:45.276 --> 49:49.654
It had a poorly-ventilated,
Third-World youth-hostel kind of charm.

49:49.781 --> 49:51.608
And there were no bodies.

49:51.741 --> 49:56.071
And of all the various and sundry stains,
none were blood or gore.

49:56.871 --> 49:59.541
I was thankful for the little things.

50:00.458 --> 50:03.578
It was official. I was on my own.

50:03.712 --> 50:10.592
I was dead, nay, undead, and not only
did I have to find a job, I had to do laundry.

50:10.719 --> 50:12.676
This was my so-called afterlife.

50:12.804 --> 50:15.924
Hypnotised by the soapy swirl
of all-temperature cheer,

50:16.057 --> 50:20.766
it occurred to me if I were alive,
my mom would be washing my sheets.

50:20.895 --> 50:25.023
They would magically appear on my bed,
crisp, clean and tucked in.

50:25.150 --> 50:28.186
Those days were over. It was all over.

50:28.319 --> 50:33.694
That didn't make it any easier to move on,
even though life had moved on without me.

50:52.635 --> 50:55.672
I felt like a pervert peeping from the shadows.

50:55.805 --> 50:59.470
I could see her, but she couldn't see me.

51:07.567 --> 51:09.856
Goddamn, she's selling my shit.

51:13.448 --> 51:15.108
Can I help you?

51:16.993 --> 51:20.243
- How much?
- That shouldn't be out here.

51:20.372 --> 51:26.291
It's got a sticker on it. 775...
You were gonna sell Frankenfruity for 775 cents?

51:26.419 --> 51:29.504
Who says you can't put a price
on childhood memories?

51:29.631 --> 51:32.798
- It's a mistake. It's not for sale.
- Why not?

51:33.551 --> 51:37.881
- 'Cause I changed my mind.
- I'll give you... five bucks for it.

51:38.556 --> 51:43.265
- I told you, it's not for sale.
- It's just a stupid toy.

51:43.395 --> 51:47.807
It was my daughter's, she's dead.
Now give me the fuckin' doll!

51:47.941 --> 51:53.279
I never heard my mom say the
F-word before. My ears were actually ringing.

51:55.115 --> 51:57.570
- Where did she get it?
- What?

51:57.701 --> 52:01.864
Frankenfruity.
I've been looking for one for a long time.

52:03.039 --> 52:07.167
She got it at a yard sale
when she was a little girl.

52:07.293 --> 52:11.920
- I doubt they make 'em now. Try eBay.
- How did your daughter die?

52:14.009 --> 52:17.378
I don't think
I wanna have this conversation with you.

52:17.512 --> 52:20.181
Well... what was she like?

52:23.518 --> 52:25.760
Why do you care?

52:26.813 --> 52:30.680
I just think it's cool she had the doll.

52:30.817 --> 52:33.059
Frankenfruity is the shit.

52:36.197 --> 52:39.613
- She drove me crazy, if you want the truth.
- What?

52:40.827 --> 52:42.903
She was stubborn.

52:43.955 --> 52:47.122
I think that's only because she was smart.

52:47.250 --> 52:49.622
Only too smart.

52:50.420 --> 52:55.841
She figured a lot of things out
way before her friends, that's for sure.

52:59.095 --> 53:01.337
We never really got along.

53:03.099 --> 53:06.551
I don't think I was a very good mother.

53:12.734 --> 53:18.404
If you want the goddamn doll, have it till
you find one, then I want this back. Understood?

53:20.283 --> 53:22.988
- Five dollars.
- It says 775 cents.

53:23.119 --> 53:28.280
You offered me five dollars.
You'll get it back when you return my doll.

53:40.887 --> 53:45.099
You need to leave now. You're making me tired.

53:49.646 --> 53:51.520
Bye.

54:00.115 --> 54:05.109
It was the longest conversation
I'd had with my mother since my periods started.

54:11.668 --> 54:14.159
And she didn't even know it was me.

54:32.105 --> 54:34.263
Get up!

54:34.899 --> 54:36.607
- Come on.
- Mom?

54:36.735 --> 54:38.526
No, not your mother.

54:38.653 --> 54:40.812
- Oh, fuck.
- What?

54:40.947 --> 54:43.734
I was hoping it was all a dream.

54:45.577 --> 54:47.902
You get dressed.

55:02.344 --> 55:05.214
- Did you get yourself a place to stay?
- Yeah.

55:05.347 --> 55:07.672
- I found a new place too.
- Yeah?

55:07.807 --> 55:09.930
Very nicely equipped, all the amenities.

55:10.060 --> 55:14.852
A Jacuzzi tub, walk-in closet
with shoes for days, and a king-size bed.

55:14.981 --> 55:18.849
- It's all about the mattress.
- Simmons, Terrace Hill, for the infirm.

55:18.985 --> 55:22.188
- You bitch.
- Babies don't sleep that good, can't afford to.

55:23.698 --> 55:26.189
So... did the waitress come back?

55:26.326 --> 55:28.484
Damn. I am thirsty.

55:29.412 --> 55:31.737
You don't mind, do you?

55:32.916 --> 55:34.992
Banana Bonanzas all around.

55:35.126 --> 55:39.338
- I was gonna have...
- The man said Banana Bonanzas all around.

55:42.592 --> 55:45.676
Banana Bonanza
and can I have more juice, please?

55:45.804 --> 55:48.295
And some water.

55:50.558 --> 55:52.634
- Bless you.
- Excuse me.

55:56.231 --> 56:02.269
- Do your nipples get hard when you sneeze?
- I, uh... don't know.

56:02.404 --> 56:06.567
- Mine do. I could put an eye out. Yours?
- Like little diamonds.

56:06.700 --> 56:10.567
Mine are always hard. I'm not sure why.

56:10.787 --> 56:13.704
I already did this guy.

56:13.832 --> 56:16.405
That was senior. This is junior.

56:16.543 --> 56:18.582
Oh. That's sad.

56:18.712 --> 56:22.081
- Should've died together, saved you a journey.
- Really though.

56:23.008 --> 56:26.875
Peanut, feel up to taking a soul today?

56:29.973 --> 56:31.348
Not really.

56:34.060 --> 56:36.100
That's too bad.

56:45.530 --> 56:47.819
Time to bust that cherry.

56:50.952 --> 56:54.286
2B or not 2B? That's the question.

56:55.790 --> 56:59.455
And for one unlucky passenger
on Coastal Link Express,

56:59.586 --> 57:02.291
it turns out I have the answer.

57:02.422 --> 57:05.921
- How do I know who?
- Car six, seat four, travelling alone.

57:06.051 --> 57:08.802
Make sure they stay in their seat.

57:14.851 --> 57:19.145
ETD is 77.277. It's gonna be violent,
so pop the soul out quick.

57:19.272 --> 57:21.561
- How violent?
- Wear your seat belt.

57:21.691 --> 57:23.767
Do trains have seat belts?

57:25.070 --> 57:28.154
- I don't think they do.
- I'm gonna vomit.

57:31.201 --> 57:35.779
Look, the first one's never easy.
I remember mine. Damn fool.

57:35.914 --> 57:37.538
He was almost vaporised.

57:37.665 --> 57:42.162
It took me ages
to find a piece big enough to pull the soul out.

57:42.295 --> 57:45.415
- What if something goes wrong?
- Well, you're already dead.

57:46.675 --> 57:48.833
- That's so not funny.
- You'll be fine.

57:48.968 --> 57:51.460
Just do everything like I showed you.

57:51.596 --> 57:55.380
- I'll see you at the next stop.
- All aboard!

58:01.523 --> 58:03.183
I was on autopilot.

58:03.316 --> 58:09.022
Every time my body took a step, my mind
screamed for it to stop and run the other way.

58:09.155 --> 58:13.367
But I kept walking.
I wondered who it was going to be.

58:13.493 --> 58:17.028
And how they planned
to get home from the train station.

58:17.163 --> 58:22.454
Were they gonna take a taxi,
or was a loved one supposed to pick them up?

58:26.256 --> 58:32.424
If I had one wish, it would be that the person
in seat four would be detained by Security

58:32.554 --> 58:38.509
for possession of narcotic substances.
Anything to keep them from getting on the train.

58:39.602 --> 58:42.603
No such luck. We have a winner.

58:43.398 --> 58:47.396
I began to fantasise about what a bitch she was,

58:47.527 --> 58:51.276
how everybody hated her,
that she was barren, had no children...

58:51.406 --> 58:53.482
Then this happened.

58:56.703 --> 58:58.411
Her name's Kirsti.

59:07.005 --> 59:08.464
All aboard!

59:10.884 --> 59:15.427
She's in kindergarten.
She loves drawing and playing with Lego.

59:15.555 --> 59:19.006
Her favourite food
is French fries and apple sauce...

59:19.142 --> 59:21.218
.. and she has to die.

59:38.244 --> 59:40.782
This is why having a destiny sucks.

59:40.914 --> 59:44.283
I stared at her seat for what seemed like hours,

59:44.417 --> 59:47.620
thinking about
all the things I'd rather be doing, like...

59:47.754 --> 59:51.454
.. having a root canal,
or a Pap smear, or going to church.

59:58.306 --> 01:00:00.678
Sure beats flying, don't it?

01:00:00.809 --> 01:00:03.810
What? Oh, yeah, I guess.

01:00:03.937 --> 01:00:07.804
All the tequila in Mexico
couldn't get me on a plane.

01:00:07.941 --> 01:00:13.066
- When I was about your age...
- I can't talk to you now... I'm praying.

01:00:14.906 --> 01:00:16.281
Oh.

01:00:40.598 --> 01:00:44.596
If only I could close my eyes
and wish all this away,

01:00:44.728 --> 01:00:47.135
wish it into the cornfield or whatever.

01:00:52.027 --> 01:00:56.735
I'd open my eyes and I'd start over,
I'd do everything right.

01:00:56.865 --> 01:01:01.076
I wouldn't drop out of college,
work in some crap job, or die.

01:01:55.757 --> 01:01:59.007
- Hi.
- Do you work for the railroad?

01:01:59.135 --> 01:02:00.167
No.

01:02:00.303 --> 01:02:03.838
I can't talk to you
unless you work for the railroad.

01:02:03.973 --> 01:02:06.346
OK, I work for the railroad.

01:02:07.435 --> 01:02:10.009
Where's your uniform?

01:02:10.146 --> 01:02:12.269
It's at the cleaners', OK?

01:02:14.567 --> 01:02:16.893
- What's your name?
- Kirsti.

01:02:17.612 --> 01:02:20.186
I didn't know what to say.

01:02:20.323 --> 01:02:25.115
They don't cover this sort of thing
on Sesame Street. So I asked...

01:02:25.245 --> 01:02:27.118
Ever been to Sea World?

01:02:27.247 --> 01:02:29.323
Magic Mountain?

01:02:29.457 --> 01:02:32.791
- Disneyland?
- I like Donald Duck.

01:02:33.586 --> 01:02:35.544
Yeah, me too.

01:02:36.339 --> 01:02:42.294
You know how you spend all day
riding all the rides and you don't want to stop?

01:02:45.223 --> 01:02:49.766
And your parents say it's time to go home,
only you're not ready yet?

01:02:49.894 --> 01:02:55.730
You want to go on one more ride, but you can't?
And it's not fair, you're pissed off that...

01:02:57.068 --> 01:03:00.022
Is any of this making any sense?

01:03:14.961 --> 01:03:17.168
Why don't you come sit with me?

01:03:18.256 --> 01:03:20.083
Miss? Everything all right?

01:03:20.216 --> 01:03:22.886
- We're just changing seats.
- Do you know her?

01:03:23.011 --> 01:03:25.466
I don't know her.

01:03:25.597 --> 01:03:29.215
- You should go to your assigned seats.
- She'll sit with me.

01:03:44.949 --> 01:03:46.776
Sit down. Hold onto something.

01:03:46.910 --> 01:03:48.902
Mr Blinky!

01:04:30.328 --> 01:04:32.784
Everyone OK?

01:04:32.914 --> 01:04:35.666
There were ten passengers in this car.

01:04:38.003 --> 01:04:40.754
I'll count you all off.

01:04:40.880 --> 01:04:43.502
One... two...

01:04:44.300 --> 01:04:46.008
.. three...

01:04:46.136 --> 01:04:47.713
.. four...

01:04:47.846 --> 01:04:50.467
Sweet Kirsti with her baby-doll dress

01:04:50.598 --> 01:04:54.014
and patent leather Mary Janes
was alive and well.

01:04:55.061 --> 01:04:58.181
I secretly hoped
that this was grounds for a termination.

01:04:58.690 --> 01:05:02.308
-.. ten.
- That was one more than there should be.

01:05:03.069 --> 01:05:05.441
We're all here.

01:05:15.707 --> 01:05:19.657
Fortunately, the trauma
of our collective near-death experience

01:05:19.794 --> 01:05:22.581
kept conversation to a minimum.

01:05:31.973 --> 01:05:35.010
We're probably not too far from Highway 20.

01:05:35.143 --> 01:05:37.716
I'm sure rescue teams are on their way.

01:05:37.854 --> 01:05:40.772
I suggest we keep warm
and count our blessings.

01:05:40.899 --> 01:05:43.686
Miss? We should stick together.

01:05:44.736 --> 01:05:47.227
I have to pee.

01:05:47.364 --> 01:05:49.522
Stay close.

01:06:04.547 --> 01:06:07.335
- Rube, where are you?
- Keep it down.

01:06:07.467 --> 01:06:10.836
You could've told me it was a little girl, you dick!

01:06:10.970 --> 01:06:15.632
- What difference does it make?
- It makes all the difference. Why her?

01:06:15.767 --> 01:06:17.843
Why do you think?

01:06:19.521 --> 01:06:22.724
- She showed up for her appointment.
- Then you should've rescheduled.

01:06:22.857 --> 01:06:24.933
That's not how it works.

01:06:25.652 --> 01:06:28.225
You just can't change fate.

01:06:28.363 --> 01:06:30.320
I did.

01:06:32.617 --> 01:06:34.028
What did you do?

01:06:35.078 --> 01:06:36.952
What did you do?

01:06:38.498 --> 01:06:41.534
She's not dead. I didn't remove her soul.

01:06:45.797 --> 01:06:47.790
What do you think you're doing?

01:06:47.924 --> 01:06:49.715
I'm letting her live.

01:06:51.761 --> 01:06:54.881
Cardinal rule: everybody dies.

01:06:56.349 --> 01:06:59.434
You'd better march over there
and take her soul.

01:06:59.561 --> 01:07:04.602
- If you want her to die, you do it.
- Only you can. Death is non-transferable.

01:07:04.733 --> 01:07:08.565
She's your mark. Only you can do the deed.

01:07:08.695 --> 01:07:12.064
Then barring any accidents,
I'd say she has another 80 years.

01:07:12.198 --> 01:07:15.033
You believe me,
that's 80 years she doesn't want.

01:07:17.245 --> 01:07:19.653
What is that supposed to mean?

01:07:19.789 --> 01:07:24.001
Her fate was sealed when she stepped
onto that train, her soul expired.

01:07:24.127 --> 01:07:27.662
Know what happens
if you keep souls around after their time?

01:07:27.797 --> 01:07:32.459
It's like milk. Spoils.
Souls go bad in all kinds of ways.

01:07:32.594 --> 01:07:35.429
If you don't understand
the severity of the situation,

01:07:35.555 --> 01:07:39.138
why don't you consult Webster's
on the definition of "bad"?

01:07:40.977 --> 01:07:46.647
If you don't take her soul,
it will wither and die and rot inside her.

01:07:48.193 --> 01:07:50.066
I've seen it happen.

01:07:52.364 --> 01:07:55.364
Do you wish to condemn her to that?

01:07:55.492 --> 01:07:57.568
She's just a little girl.

01:07:58.620 --> 01:08:00.743
She can't die. It's cruel.

01:08:00.872 --> 01:08:02.663
It is cruel.

01:08:03.708 --> 01:08:06.828
It's cruel she'll never know what life is really like,

01:08:06.961 --> 01:08:10.710
cruel she'll miss out
on so much love and pain and beauty.

01:08:10.840 --> 01:08:16.214
I'd say it for everyone, except her. She won't
care, she'll be doing something different.

01:08:17.263 --> 01:08:19.303
That's just the way it is.

01:08:23.603 --> 01:08:26.094
I just wanted to save her.

01:08:28.024 --> 01:08:30.100
You can't.

01:08:33.113 --> 01:08:35.104
You can't save any of them.

01:08:36.157 --> 01:08:38.827
All you can do is make it easier.

01:08:40.203 --> 01:08:43.738
That may not seem like a lot, but it is.

01:08:58.721 --> 01:09:00.513
Go on.

01:09:27.792 --> 01:09:31.493
I don't know if this is what I'm supposed to say...

01:09:32.255 --> 01:09:36.584
I... I mean, you...

01:09:42.098 --> 01:09:45.099
Do me a favour, just close your eyes.

01:10:15.632 --> 01:10:21.088
# When I was just a little girl

01:10:21.221 --> 01:10:23.926
# I asked my mother

01:10:24.057 --> 01:10:26.595
# What will I be?

01:10:28.269 --> 01:10:31.852
# Will I be pretty? Will I be rich?

01:10:31.981 --> 01:10:33.891
We're gonna go for a ride.

01:10:34.025 --> 01:10:37.608
# Here's what she said to me

01:10:38.321 --> 01:10:42.401
# Que sera sera

01:10:43.827 --> 01:10:47.694
# Whatever will be will be

01:10:49.791 --> 01:10:55.627
# The future's not ours to see

01:10:55.755 --> 01:10:58.507
# Que sera sera

01:11:02.303 --> 01:11:07.215
# When I wasjust a child in school

01:11:07.350 --> 01:11:09.592
- Wait!
- You can't go where she's going.

01:11:09.728 --> 01:11:13.939
# I asked my teacher, what should I try?

01:11:15.608 --> 01:11:18.609
- What is it?
- It's not for us to know.

01:11:18.737 --> 01:11:21.524
# Should I sing songs?

01:11:21.656 --> 01:11:25.950
# This was her wise reply

01:11:26.077 --> 01:11:30.241
# Que sera sera

01:11:31.666 --> 01:11:35.995
# Whatever will be will be...

01:11:37.213 --> 01:11:39.669
As we walked into the dark unknown,

01:11:39.799 --> 01:11:44.426
or whatever you want to call it,
I thought, "Is this it?"

01:11:44.554 --> 01:11:46.630
"Is this who I am?"

01:11:46.765 --> 01:11:48.841
"Am I really a grim reaper?"

01:12:16.086 --> 01:12:19.537
I think for me, death was just a wake-up call.

01:12:36.981 --> 01:12:41.940
# When I grew up and fell in love

01:12:42.570 --> 01:12:45.275
# I asked my sweetheart

01:12:45.407 --> 01:12:47.862
# What lies ahead?

01:12:49.661 --> 01:12:54.868
# Will there be rainbows, day after day?

01:12:55.500 --> 01:12:59.332
# Here's what my sweetheart said

01:12:59.963 --> 01:13:03.581
# Que sera sera

01:13:05.301 --> 01:13:09.513
# Whatever will be will be

01:13:11.391 --> 01:13:15.436
# The future's not ours to see

